DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl",
);

##############################################

Context("LimitedNumeric");

$b=random(2,9,1);
$a=$b*random(2,9,1);
$c=random(2,9,1);

$ans=Compute($a/(-$b)*$c);


##############################################

TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML

Evaluate the expression:

    [`` [$a]\div(-[$b])[$c]=  ``]  [________]{$ans} 

END_PGML

##############################################

$pro1Step1 = $a*$b;
$pro2Step1 = $a/$b;

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

Since there is no operation symbol between [`(-[$b])`] and [`[$c]`], it implies multiplication.

We perform the operations from left to right since multiplication and division have the same priority in the order of operations.

      [``
        \begin{aligned}[t]
           [$a]\div(-[$b])[$c] & = -[$a/$b] \cdot [$c]  \\
                                 & =  [$ans] 
          \end{aligned}
      ``]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();


